@ThinkingandTinkering I can answer that one for you Robert using your own logik 😂 I have 2 x 300tdi Discos 1974/1975 they do 30 mpg whatever I throw at them cost me a couple of hundred quid a year to service (myself) being so old they are in their second cradle to grave carbon footprint so are greener than most cars around now. 7seats massive cargo space for a car and in an serious accident you call for an ambulance for the other driver😂
Paddocks land rover supply cheap parts (all four discs pads and fittings for about £100 last time) being diesel they are bad for the people that like clean air but as we have to many people in the world killing a few off with particulates is good for the plant as a whole 😂 as you are obviously doing with your 40 a day 😂 (ps not anti smoking I gave up to live longer but still love the smell when someone lights up next to me)
So with all that in mind I expect to see you shopping in a 4x4 soon  😂

@bikerfirefarter7280 Lmao, damn and I had just managed to rein in the Crazy!!
Thank you though, I love a good laugh!
Peace. XxX

@ThinkingandTinkering If smoking is so bad for you, how come it cures kippers?
And at the rate you smoke you should have lungs like black-smiths bellows.  ;-)
'Bagpipes', Ray Stevens.

@bikerfirefarter7280 No offence meant by Flatland mate just meant places like Norfolk not Welsh mountains  😁  I have owned, riden and loved Fixies in the past and like you say pick your terrain. I found the experience of the pedal pushing up harder than I could push down on 30% grades a pain 😁 and no free downhill bits keeps you fit 😁
I still have some single speeds a Jump bike (Identiti 666), BMX and a Trials bike (YaaBaa)  also 3 speed SA clunker (Muddy Fox 70's frame) a Specialized Rock Hopper hardtail (27 speed) and a Saracen Downhill full sus bike own(24 speed) most in my own custom paint jobs And for my sins a Carrera Crossfire Ebike (don't judge my 61 year old knees are shot and need help some days 😁)
If you want to expand your cycling I learnt to unicycle about 8 years ago and that is the hardest workout I have ever done especialy Muni ( Offroad 24" Quax ) and I'm still Bl**dy useless at it 😁

